  "notes": [
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "## 双眼鏡の使い方\n\n- 初心者には **8倍** が最適（8x32 や 8x42）\n- まず肉眼で鳥を見つけてから、視線を動かさずに双眼鏡を目に持っていく\n- ピント合わせはゆっくり回す。素早く回すと見失いやすい\n- レンズの汚れはブロアーで吹き飛ばし、レンズペンで拭く",
        "en": "## Binocular Tips\n\n- **8x magnification** is ideal for beginners (8x32 or 8x42)\n- First locate the bird with your naked eye, then bring binoculars up without moving your gaze\n- Adjust focus slowly — fast turns make it easy to lose the bird\n- Clean lenses with a blower first, then a lens pen"
      },
      "url": "https://www.wbsj.org/activity/spread-and-education/birding-guide/"
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "## 観察のベストシーズン\n\n- **春（3〜5月）**: 夏鳥の渡来、シギチドリの春の渡り\n- **夏（6〜8月）**: 繁殖期、さえずりが最も活発\n- **秋（9〜11月）**: シギチドリの秋の渡り、冬鳥の渡来\n- **冬（12〜2月）**: カモ類が最も多い、猛禽類も観察しやすい\n- 年間を通じて楽しめるが、**早朝**（日の出〜午前中）が最も活発",
        "en": "## Best Observation Seasons\n\n- **Spring (Mar–May)**: Summer visitors arrive, shorebird spring migration\n- **Summer (Jun–Aug)**: Breeding season, most active singing\n- **Autumn (Sep–Nov)**: Shorebird autumn migration, winter visitors arrive\n- **Winter (Dec–Feb)**: Most ducks present, raptors easier to spot\n- Birding is year-round, but **early morning** (sunrise to noon) is most active"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "## 早朝の観察テクニック\n\n- 日の出前に現地に到着するのが理想的\n- **静かに移動**し、鳥の警戒を避ける\n- 地味な色の服装を着用（迷彩柄は不要、グレーやカーキでOK）\n- 同じ場所に **15〜20分** じっと待つと、鳥が慣れて近くに来る\n- 鳴き声で種類を判別できると、観察効率が大幅にアップ",
        "en": "## Morning Observation Tips\n\n- Arrive at the site before sunrise ideally\n- **Move quietly** to avoid alarming birds\n- Wear muted colors (camouflage is unnecessary — grey or khaki works)\n- Stay still in one spot for **15–20 minutes** and birds will come closer\n- Learning bird calls greatly improves identification efficiency"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "## フィールドノートの取り方\n\n記録すべき項目:\n1. **日時・天候・気温**\n2. **場所**（GPS座標があると便利）\n3. **種名・個体数**\n4. **行動**（採餌、さえずり、飛翔方向など）\n5. **特徴**（不明種のスケッチや色のメモ）\n\nスマートフォンの野鳥記録アプリ（eBird等）を併用すると、データの蓄積と共有が容易",
        "en": "## Field Notes Guide\n\nKey items to record:\n1. **Date, time, weather, temperature**\n2. **Location** (GPS coordinates are helpful)\n3. **Species name and count**\n4. **Behavior** (feeding, singing, flight direction, etc.)\n5. **Features** (sketch or color notes for unidentified birds)\n\nUse a bird recording app (e.g., eBird) alongside to easily accumulate and share data"
      },
      "url": "https://ebird.org/"
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "## バードウォッチングのマナー\n\n- **巣に近づかない** — 繁殖期は特に注意。親鳥が巣を放棄する原因になる\n- **録音した鳴き声の再生は控えめに** — 鳥にストレスを与える\n- **私有地に無断で立ち入らない**\n- **ゴミは必ず持ち帰る**\n- **他の観察者への配慮** — 大声を出さない、観察の邪魔をしない\n- 希少種の営巣場所をSNSに公開しない",
        "en": "## Birding Etiquette\n\n- **Don't approach nests** — especially during breeding season, as it can cause nest abandonment\n- **Limit playback of recorded calls** — it stresses birds\n- **Don't trespass on private property**\n- **Take all trash with you**\n- **Be considerate of other birders** — keep quiet, don't block others' views\n- Don't share rare nesting locations on social media"
      }
    }
  ]
}
